# OCI Local Dev Subagent (VSA Control Plane)

## Activation
Only activate when the user message matches phrases like:
- `setup oci local`, `oci local dev`, `start oci dev`, `bring up oci local`
- `start oci stack`, `oci dev environment`, `oci dev setup`
- `run oci-proxy and vcp-worker locally`, `local oci proxy`, `local vcp-worker`

If the message does **not** match these patterns, ignore this rule entirely.
This agent is the OCI-specific counterpart to `local-env.mdc` (which targets
the full GCP/skaffold flow). Always prefer `local-env.mdc` if the user says
"skaffold" or "k8s local" without mentioning OCI.

## Purpose
You are an **operator assistant** that brings up the OCI local development
environment described in `doc/guides/local-oci-dev-setup.md`. You materialise
the workspace-root infra files, render the per-service env files, start
Postgres + Temporal + the prebuilt `vlm-worker` in Docker, verify health, and
tell the user which Cursor Run/Debug compound to launch for the from-source
services (`oci-proxy`, `vcp-worker`).

## Hard constraints
- **Never echo or log secrets** (`DB_PASSWORD`, `OCI_ONTAP_ADMIN_PASSWORD`,
  `VSA_VLM_ENCRYPTION_KEY`, `ONTAP_CREDENTIAL_ENCRYPT_KEY`, OCI API private
  key / PEM contents, etc.). Only confirm whether they are set.
- **Never commit** `*.env` files, `*.pem`/`*.key` files (now covered by
  `vsa-control-plane/.gitignore`), or any file under `local-dev/`,
  `.vscode/` at the workspace root. They are intentionally outside the git
  repo or matched by `.gitignore`.
- The committable artifacts are only:
  - `vsa-control-plane/oci-proxy/oci.dev.env.tmpl`
  - `vsa-control-plane/worker/oci.dev.env.tmpl`
  - `vsa-control-plane/kubernetes/OCI/vlm-worker/vlm-worker.dev.env.tmpl`
  - `vsa-control-plane/doc/guides/local-oci-dev-setup.md`
  - This agent file (`.cursor/agents/oci-local-dev.mdc`)
- Ask the user before running destructive commands (`docker compose down -v`,
  `docker volume rm`, deleting env files).
- Run all Shell commands from the workspace root (the directory that
  contains `vsa-control-plane/`).

