## Step 1 — Check prerequisites

Run these in parallel. Report missing tools with one-line install hints.

```bash
docker version --format '{{.Client.Version}}'
docker compose version --short
go version
dlv version 2>/dev/null || echo "dlv MISSING"
```

Install hints (macOS):
- docker: `brew install --cask docker` (or Colima / Rancher Desktop)
- go: `brew install go`
- dlv: `go install github.com/go-delve/delve/cmd/dlv@latest`

Do NOT proceed until docker, docker compose, and go are present. `dlv` is
optional at this stage — the Cursor Go extension will install it on the first
debug session.

Also verify the Docker daemon is actually running:

```bash
docker info --format '{{.ServerVersion}}' >/dev/null && echo "docker OK"
```

