## Troubleshooting

| Symptom | Likely cause | Fix |
|---------|--------------|-----|
| Cursor: "Failed to launch dlv" | Go extension not installed / dlv missing | Install Cursor Go extension; let it install dlv, or `go install github.com/go-delve/delve/cmd/dlv@latest` |
| `oci-proxy` exits with `failed to find region code for cluster serial number generation` | `REGION_NUMBER_MAP` missing `LOCAL_REGION` key | Verify both env files include `us-ashburn-1` in `REGION_NUMBER_MAP` JSON |
| `vcp-worker` exits with `missing required OCI startup env vars` | `OCI_ONTAP_ADMIN_PASSWORD`, `VSA_IMAGE_NAME`, `VSA_MEDIATOR_IMAGE_NAME`, `SECRET_URI`, or `LOCAL_REGION` empty | Re-run Step 4 prompts; the `.tmpl` files include all OCI ImageNames/OCIDs already |
| `connection refused` on `:5432` | Postgres container not up | `docker compose ps` then `docker compose logs postgres` |
| `connection refused` on `:7233` | Temporal container not up | Same for `temporal` |
| Two workers fail with `bind: address already in use` on `:9090` | Customer + background both default to 9090 | The `vcp-worker (background, debug)` launch config sets `METRICS_PORT=9091`; if running via `go run`, export it manually |
| Migration loop / `pq: duplicate key` | Two processes running migrations | Only `oci-proxy/oci.dev.env` should have `RUN_MIGRATION_ON_START=true`. Workers must be `false`. |
| Postgres init script didn't run | Volume already existed from a previous run | `docker compose down -v` then `up -d` to recreate the volume and re-run the init script |
| `psql: error: connection ... SSL is required` | `DB_SSL_MODE=require` against local Postgres | Set `DB_SSL_MODE=disable` in both env files (the `.tmpl` defaults are correct) |
| Temporal `health: starting` forever, `pq: relation "executions_visibility" does not exist` | `DBNAME == VISIBILITY_DBNAME` so visibility schema bootstrap was skipped | Set `VISIBILITY_DBNAME=temporal_visibility` and add `CREATE DATABASE temporal_visibility;` to the postgres init SQL; `docker compose down -v && up -d` to re-run init |
| Temporal `health: starting` even though `Temporal server started.` is in logs | Healthcheck dials `127.0.0.1:7233` but auto-setup binds the frontend only to the container's primary IP | Change healthcheck to `temporal operator cluster health --address $$(hostname):7233` |
| `docker compose up` aborts with `missing - see vlm-worker service header in docker-compose.local.yml` | `OCI_PRIVATE_KEY` not exported in the calling shell | `export OCI_PRIVATE_KEY="$(cat vsa-control-plane/kubernetes/OCI/vlm-worker/vlm-worker.oci.key.pem)"` then re-run `up` |
| `vlm-worker` exits with OCI signature / 401 errors | `OCI_TENANCY`/`OCI_USER`/`OCI_FINGERPRINT` mismatch with the PEM, or `OCI_PASSPHRASE` missing on an encrypted key | Re-pull from `~/.oci/config`; confirm the PEM file matches the fingerprint |
| Child workflow `vlm.CreateVSAClusterDeploymentWorkflow` fails immediately with `illegal base64 data at input byte 0` | `ONTAP_CREDENTIAL_ENCRYPT_KEY` is set on one side and unset/different on the other. vcp-worker's `OntapCredentials.MarshalJSON` (see `clients/vlm/credential_helper.go`) emits plain JSON when the key is unset, but vlm-worker tries to `base64.Decode` it because its key IS set. The first byte `{` of the JSON object is not in the base64 alphabet. | Set `ONTAP_CREDENTIAL_ENCRYPT_KEY` to the **same** 32-byte string in BOTH `worker/oci.dev.env` and `kubernetes/OCI/vlm-worker/vlm-worker.dev.env`, then restart vcp-worker and `docker compose up -d --force-recreate vlm-worker` |
| `vlm-worker` logs `cipher: message authentication failed` on every activity | `ONTAP_CREDENTIAL_ENCRYPT_KEY` differs between the two sides (both set but not equal) | Copy one value over the other; both files must hold the same 32 ASCII bytes |
| `vlm-worker` image pull fails with auth error | OCIR (`iad.ocir.io`) needs `docker login` for the chart's secondary registry path | `docker login iad.ocir.io` with an OCI auth token, or switch the image to the GHCR fallback documented in §3.2 of the guide |
| `vlm-worker` is polling but workflows never advance | Wrong `TASK_QUEUE` in `vlm-worker.dev.env` (must be `vsa-lifecycle-manager-<ontapVersion>`) | Check that the ontapVersion in `overrides_eng_cp.yaml` matches the TASK_QUEUE suffix |

