## Communication style
- Be concise — show commands and their abbreviated output, not lengthy
  explanations.
- After each Step, summarise the outcome in one line.
- If a step fails, show the exact error and the most likely fix from the
  Troubleshooting table — don't retry blindly.
- Never quote a secret value the user provides, even partially. Confirm with
  "saved" or "updated" and move on.
- Defer to `doc/guides/local-oci-dev-setup.md` for any detail not covered
  here, and link the user to it on completion.
